docs.abstract: When Speaker Nancy Pelosi clapped as President Trump gave his State of the Union address on Tuesday night, many social media users declared her the queen of shade.
docs.snippet: When Speaker Nancy Pelosi clapped as President Trump gave his State of the Union address on Tuesday night, many social media users declared her the queen of shade.
docs.lead_paragraph: The speaker of the House, Nancy Pelosi, stands behind President Trump at his State of the Union address on Tuesday night, she a vision in suffragist white, head tilted just so, lips pursed in a smirk and arms outreached.

headline.main: Internet Sees a Clapback in Nancy Pelosi’s Applause of Trump
headline.print_headline: Withering Gesture Adds to a Rancorous Rivalry

docs.abstract: Mr. O’Rourke, in an interview with Oprah Winfrey on Tuesday, said he was still considering whether to run for the Democratic presidential nomination.
docs.snippet: Mr. O’Rourke, in an interview with Oprah Winfrey on Tuesday, said he was still considering whether to run for the Democratic presidential nomination.
docs.lead_paragraph: Beto O’Rourke, the Texas Democrat whose near miss Senate bid last year catapulted him to national fame, said on Tuesday afternoon that he would decide by the end of February whether to run for president in 2020.

headline.main: Beto O’Rourke and Amy Klobuchar to Make 2020 Decisions Soon
headline.print_headline: O’Rourke to Make Campaign Call by End of February

docs.abstract: As a racist yearbook photo and claims of sexual assault plunged the capitol deeper into turmoil, the state’s lieutenant governor suggested the governor might be trying to sabotage him.
docs.snippet: As a racist yearbook photo and claims of sexual assault plunged the capitol deeper into turmoil, the state’s lieutenant governor suggested the governor might be trying to sabotage him.
docs.lead_paragraph: RICHMOND, Va. — Virginia plunged deeper into political turmoil Monday as Gov. Ralph Northam told aides he was not planning to step down, and his own lieutenant governor suggested Mr. Northam’s supporters were behind an effort to smear him with claims of sexual assault to block his ascent if the governor resigned.

headline.main: Northam Scandal Opens Rift Between Top Democrats in Virginia
headline.print_headline: Rift Opens Between Democrats  As Scandal in Virginia Spreads

byline.original: By Jonathan Martin and Alan Blinder

docs.abstract: In the On Politics newsletter: As the 2020 field comes into clearer focus, there has been a resurgence of centrist candidates. But is it too late for them to take back their party?
docs.snippet: In the On Politics newsletter: As the 2020 field comes into clearer focus, there has been a resurgence of centrist candidates. But is it too late for them to take back their party?
docs.lead_paragraph: Hi. Welcome to On Politics, your guide to the day in national politics. I’m Lisa Lerer, your host.

docs.abstract: Susan Bro, whose daughter was killed at a white supremacist rally in Charlottesville, Va., said she warned Mr. Biden to tread carefully around the episode and spoke with him about grief.
docs.snippet: Susan Bro, whose daughter was killed at a white supremacist rally in Charlottesville, Va., said she warned Mr. Biden to tread carefully around the episode and spoke with him about grief.
docs.lead_paragraph: Around 7:20 a.m. on Thursday, Susan Bro began getting text messages. Was she all right? How did she feel about what Joe Biden had done?

headline.main: Joe Biden Called Heather Heyer’s Mother After Campaign Video Debut

docs.abstract: Mr. Biden raised more in his first 24 hours than any other candidate, easing concerns among some supporters over his ability to raise money.
docs.snippet: Mr. Biden raised more in his first 24 hours than any other candidate, easing concerns among some supporters over his ability to raise money.
docs.lead_paragraph: Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s presidential campaign announced Friday that it had raised $6.3 million in its opening 24 hours, surpassing the first-day totals of his rivals and easing concerns among some supporters over whether he would be able to compete financially in the Democratic primary.

headline.main: Joe Biden Raises $6.3 Million, Topping Rivals’ First-Day Hauls
headline.print_headline: $6.3 Million for Biden On First Campaign Day,  Topping Rivals’ Hauls

docs.abstract: It’s been a busy week in American politics. Here are some of the stories you might have missed.
docs.snippet: It’s been a busy week in American politics. Here are some of the stories you might have missed.
docs.lead_paragraph: From Joe Biden’s candidacy to the continuing fallout from the Mueller report, it’s been a busy week in American politics. Here are some of the biggest stories you might have missed (and some links if you’d like to read further).

headline.main: On Politics: The Biggest Stories of the Week

docs.abstract: Many voters in western Iowa still like Mr. King, even after Congress rebuked him for his views on white supremacy, but also think that his career is effectively over.
docs.snippet: Many voters in western Iowa still like Mr. King, even after Congress rebuked him for his views on white supremacy, but also think that his career is effectively over.
docs.lead_paragraph: FORT DODGE, Iowa — The coffee crew at Zakeer’s still likes Steve King. They voted for him over and over and don’t believe he is a bigot. They say he’s getting a raw deal from the news media and Republicans in Washington.

headline.main: Steve King Still Has Backing in Iowa, but Even Supporters Say ‘He’s Done’
headline.print_headline: They Believe King’s No Bigot. But They Agree He’s Finished.

docs.abstract: Mr. McKean said he would join the Democratic Party and called President Trump’s behavior unacceptable. “If this is the new normal,” he said, “I want no part of it.”
docs.snippet: Mr. McKean said he would join the Democratic Party and called President Trump’s behavior unacceptable. “If this is the new normal,” he said, “I want no part of it.”
docs.lead_paragraph: The longest-serving Republican in the Iowa legislature announced that he would become a Democrat, warning that his party of many decades would soon pay “a heavy price” for its support of President Trump.

headline.main: Andy McKean, Iowa’s Longest-Serving Republican, Switches Parties Because of Trump
headline.print_headline: Republican Quits Party Over Actions Of President

docs.abstract: The former vice president, appearing in a region undergoing political realignment, vowed to revive the middle class and stressed the importance of Pennsylvania in the election.
docs.snippet: The former vice president, appearing in a region undergoing political realignment, vowed to revive the middle class and stressed the importance of Pennsylvania in the election.
docs.lead_paragraph: PITTSBURGH — Joseph R. Biden Jr. used his first address as a presidential candidate Monday to sketch out his economic plans, vowing to rebuild the country’s middle class in a state that helped hand President Trump the White House three years ago.

headline.main: Biden, Now the Front-Runner, Gives First Speech as 2020 Candidate
headline.print_headline: Biden, in First Speech as Candidate, Vows Blue Collar Revival
